      "id": "GENUS_ANTHUS",
      "name": "Anthus",
      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "Pipits — streaky brown passerines of open habitats, the sparrows of the moor and meadow. Pipits can be difficult to identify by plumage but their songs and calls are distinctive — the meadow pipit gives a thin, insistent 'seep' in flight. The tree pipit (trädpiplärka) sings a wonderful descending song, delivered in a parachuting display flight from a tree perch — one of the joyful sounds of Swedish woodland clearings in spring. Meadow pipits are extraordinarily numerous across Scandinavian moorland and bogland and are the primary host of the common cuckoo in many areas. Pipits walk (rather than hop) and wag their tails gently, unlike the more vigorous pumping of true wagtails.",
      "lineage": "Pipits",
